AS Roma on Thursday signed Nigerian defender, Osinachi Ohale, from Real Madrid. Ohale, 28, has featured for the Super Falcons at three FIFA World Cups. She is now the third signing for Roma as they prepare for the 2020-2021 season. Roma had already signed Italian goalkeeper, Rachele Baldi and Spanish forward, Paloma Lazaro. “Welcome to the team, Osinachi Ohale!” the club said on its official Twitter account. “The Nigerian defender becomes our latest addition this summer!” Reacting, Ohale told the club’s official website: “I chose Roma because of so many things; so many amazing things about the club, about this city and this country that interested me. “I felt like it would be a great thing for me, to explore and to experience new things and a new challenge.”